Reasoning: The paper discusses an agent-based model of topic mobility behavior of scholars in the scientific community. This model can be applied to various fields, but the focus of the paper is on scientific production and academic society. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other likely sub-categories include cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks), cs.DL (Digital Libraries), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
